      "ajv package source"
    ],
    "notes": [
      "Ajv v8 exports the class as both 'Ajv' and 'default'. Invariants use class: 'default'.",
      "The typical pattern is: new Ajv() → instance; instance.compile(schema) → validateFn; validateFn(data) → boolean.",
      "node_constructor_call_eq with then_call: true handles the compile+validate two-step.",
      "validateSchema() is a single-step method call (no then_call).",
      "allErrors option makes Ajv collect all errors rather than stopping at the first."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-04-02T00:00:00Z",
